com.orgsync.api

Interface ApiResponse<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the successful response

    public interface ApiResponse<T>

    A response from the API, which may be either success or failure. Use the isSuccess() method to determine if this request was successful. If its a success, then getResult() will return the result object. It its a failure, then getError() will return the ApiError.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      ApiError getError()
      Get the error from this response if not isSuccess().
      T getResult()
      Get the result from this response if it isSuccess().
      int getStatus()
      Get the status code that was returned from this request.
      boolean isSuccess()
      Return whether this response is a success or not.
